    <text>
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="cww.00372.001.jpg"/>
            <div1 type="petition" subtype="handwritten">
                    <p>To. the Emancipation Commissioners.&#8212;</p>
                    <p>I <persName>Catharine A. M. Maddox</persName> reside <address><addrLine>Corner of N.
                            3d Streets East 5th Ward <placeName>Washington City D C</placeName></addrLine></address></p>
                    <p>State that at the time of the passage of the <hi rend="underline">act</hi> I
                        held a claim for the <hi rend="underline">service</hi> or <choice><orig>labour</orig><reg>labor</reg></choice> of a <hi
                            rend="underline">person</hi> of African descent&#8212;<persName>Mary E.
                            McKinsy</persName> a Mulatto <hi rend="underline">woman</hi> she is <hi
                            rend="underline">five</hi> ft. one <hi rend="underline">inch</hi> in <hi
                            rend="underline">height</hi> thought very good looking&#8212;she <hi
                            rend="underline">has</hi> fine <hi rend="underline">suit</hi> of <hi
                            rend="underline">hair</hi> good teeth and <hi rend="underline">figure</hi> (age) I obtained from the <hi rend="underline"><hi
                                rend="underline">Inventory</hi></hi> &#38; Appraisement of the good's &#38; Chattels and personal estate, of my <hi rend="underline">father</hi>
                        <persName>William R. Maddox</persName> late of <placeName>Washington
                            County</placeName> (deceased) <hi rend="underline">as</hi> made by <persName>Griffith <hi
                                rend="underline">Combe</hi></persName>&#8212;and <persName>Thomas
                            Blagden</persName> on <date notBefore="1838-01-10" notAfter="1838-01-11">10th &#38; 11th of January 1838</date>; Under authority from the
                        Judge of the Orphan's <hi rend="underline">Court</hi> of said County said
                            <hi rend="underline">woman</hi>, <persName>Mary E.
                        McKinsy</persName>&#8212;was then a child 3. <hi rend="underline">years</hi>
                        <hi rend="underline">old</hi>&#8212;I heired <hi rend="underline">her</hi>
                        <hi rend="underline">from</hi> that <hi rend="underline">Estate</hi>&#8212;she is now in her 27th year&#8212;&#8212;I also hold a
                        claim for the service or <hi rend="underline"><choice><orig>labour</orig><reg>labor</reg></choice></hi>, of her
                            daughter&#8212;<persName>Charlotte</persName>, <persName>K. E.
                            McKinsy</persName>
                        <hi rend="underline">who</hi> was <choice>
                            <sic>borned</sic>
                            <corr>born</corr>
                        </choice> on <date when="1856-04-04">4th of <hi rend="underline">Apl</hi> 1856</date>, she is <hi rend="underline">now</hi> in <hi
                            rend="underline">her</hi> 7th <hi rend="underline">year</hi>&#8212;a
                        very smart <hi rend="underline">girl</hi></p>
                    <p>I <hi rend="underline">have</hi>
                        <hi rend="underline">been</hi> offered repeatedly for mother &#38;
                        daughter fifteen <hi rend="underline">hundred</hi>
                        <hi rend="underline">dollars</hi> in <hi rend="underline">cash</hi>&#8212;<hi rend="underline">as</hi> <persName>Mary E. McKinsy</persName> will <hi rend="underline">swear She</hi> is worth that to <hi rend="underline">me</hi> she is a
                        valuable <hi rend="underline">servant</hi> for her work <hi rend="underline">as</hi> I <hi rend="underline">can</hi>
                        <hi rend="underline">prove</hi>.</p>
                
                    <p>I further state That I <hi rend="underline">am</hi> a true &#38; <hi
                            rend="underline">loyal</hi> Citizen of the <placeName>United
                            States</placeName>, and have not borne Arm's Against them during the present <choice>
                            <sic>rebelion</sic>
                            <corr>rebellion</corr>
                        </choice> or in any way given <hi rend="underline">aid</hi> or comfort
                        thereto</p>
                    <p>I have not <hi rend="underline">brought</hi> the <hi rend="underline">slave</hi> into the <hi rend="underline">district</hi> since the <hi
                            rend="underline">passage</hi>
                        <hi rend="underline">over</hi>
                        <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="cww.00372.002.jpg"/>of this act&#8212;I further
                        state that the <hi rend="underline">Claim <choice>
                            <sic>dos</sic>
                            <corr>does</corr>
                            </choice></hi> not originate by virtue of any transfer made by any <hi
                            rend="underline">person</hi> who <hi rend="underline">has</hi> in any
                        manner aided or sustained the rebellion against the <placeName>United
                            States</placeName>&#8212;I <hi rend="underline">close</hi> by asking the
                            <hi rend="underline">Board</hi> to determine the validity of the <hi
                            rend="underline">Claim</hi> and report the same to the Secretary of the
                        Treasury in conformity with the provisions of the Act</p>
                    <closer><signed><persName>Catharine A. M. Maddox</persName></signed></closer>
                </div1>

                <div1 type="oath" subtype="handwritten">
                <div2 type="section">
                    <dateline><placeName>Washington County</placeName><lb/>
                        <placeName>District of Columbia</placeName> To wit</dateline>
                    <p>I <persName>Catharine A. M. Maddox</persName> being Duly Sworn do depose and
                        Say, that all the Several Matters and things which are set forth and stated
                        in the <choice><orig>foregoin</orig><reg>foregoing</reg></choice> petition, as of my own knowledge are true in substance and fact and that all the several other matters and things therein set forth and
                        stated as from the information of Others I believe to be true in Substance and in
                        fact</p>
                    <closer><signed><persName>Catharine A. M. Maddox</persName></signed></closer>
                </div2>
                    
                <div2 type="section">
                    <p>Sworn to and Subscribed <hi rend="underline">before</hi> me this <date when="1862-05-22">22d day of May 1862</date></p>
                    <closer><signed><persName>Wm R. Woodwoard</persName> clerk &#38;c</signed></closer>
                </div2>
                </div1>
            
